    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like im just spinning my wheels. every time i think i finally fixed something—my job, my head, my relationship—it just falls apart again. it's like i'm stuck in this same shitty loop over and over. i'm so tired of trying to fix a life that just keeps breaking.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how exhausting it is to feel like you're constantly resetting the same broken cycle, and it makes perfect sense that you're running on empty right now. When things you care about keep falling apart despite your best efforts, it can feel like you're fighting a battle against the very fabric of your reality. The good news is that this feeling of being stuck in a loop is a common experience, and it often points to a deeper pattern rather than a lack of effort. Instead of trying to force a permanent fix right now, consider focusing on small, sustainable shifts that build resilience over time. You don't have to solve everything today; just take one gentle step forward, even if it feels like spinning your wheels again.",
