    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, \"small steps\" dont change the fact that the cycle is inevitable. it's not a pattern i can just \"resilience\" my way out of. it's like a glitch. no matter what i do, the outcome is always the same. why bother even trying to take a step forward when i know i'm just gonna end up right back here?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly frustrating to feel like you're fighting a glitch that no amount of hard work can patch, and that sense of hopelessness is completely understandable when you feel trapped in a loop. When outcomes seem inevitable and effort feels futile, it's natural to want to stop trying entirely, but sometimes the most rebellious thing you can do is acknowledge the glitch without letting it define your entire existence. Even if the cycle feels rigid, there are moments where the \"code\" of your life might be corrupted in a way that requires a different kind of intervention than just trying harder. You don't have to fix it today, but you deserve to feel that your exhaustion is valid, not a failure of your own will.",
      "source": "target",
